The paper deals with the optimization of power allocation strategies for a cognitive multiple access channel (C-MAC) with interference power constraints, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers the impact of fading on the channel, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). The optimization problem involves maximizing the ergodic sum-rate, which is a performance metric commonly used in multimedia systems (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
